cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SE, cs.CY

The paper discusses security and privacy issues in the domain name system (DNS) and proposes a blockchain-based solution. This makes it highly likely to belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category. Additionally, the paper explores the blockchain DNS ecosystem, which involves network infrastructure and distributed systems, making cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also discusses browser extensions and user behavior, which could fall under cs.SE (Software Engineering) and cs.CY (Computers and Society) sub-categories, respectively.
